.TH AUXTOP 1 "June 2026" "A/UX Workstation" "Local Commands"
.SH NAME
auxtop \- themed real-time process monitor for A/UX
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B auxtop
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B auxtop
is an htop-inspired ncurses process monitor for A/UX 3.1.1.  It reads
the kernel through
.I /dev/kmem
via the machine-dependent module from top 3.5 and renders live CPU,
memory, and swap meters above a process table sorted by size.
.PP
The A/UX cpustate order is
.IR idle,user,kernel,wait,nice ;
auxtop looks the idle slot up by name rather than position.
.SH KEYS
.TP
.B q
quit
.TP
.B space
refresh now
.TP
.B i
toggle idle processes
.SH THEMES
Colors come from
.I /.auxtoprc
or the file named by
.BR AUXTOP_THEME .
Keys title, text, accent, bar, header, and status take the eight ANSI
color names.  The default is the C89 SUMMER synthwave palette.
.SH FILES
/.auxtoprc, /dev/kmem
.SH SEE ALSO
dialc(1), auxfont(1), DOCUMENT(7) in /DOCUMENT
